# ğŸŒ³ 101. Symmetric Tree

ğŸ”— LeetCode Link: https://leetcode.com/problems/symmetric-tree/

---

## ğŸ“Œ Problem Summary

Given the root of a binary tree, check whether it is a **mirror of itself**.

A tree is symmetric if:
- Left subtree is a mirror of right subtree
- Values and structure both match in mirror form

---

## ğŸ§  Core Idea â€” Mirror Comparison

Instead of comparing left with left:

âŒ left â†” left  
âŒ right â†” right  

We compare crosswise:

âœ… left â†” right  
âœ… right â†” left  

---

## âœ… Recursive Java Solution

```java
class Solution {

    public boolean isSymmetric(TreeNode root) {
        if (root == null) return true;
        return isMirror(root.left, root.right);
    }

    private boolean isMirror(TreeNode t1, TreeNode t2) {

        if (t1 == null && t2 == null) return true;

        if (t1 == null || t2 == null) return false;

        if (t1.val != t2.val) return false;

        return isMirror(t1.left, t2.right) &&
               isMirror(t1.right, t2.left);
    }
}
